FUNDING OPPORTUNITY NO  P22AS00103   FY 2022 NATIVE AMERICAN GRAVES PROTECTION AND REPATRIATION ACT  NAGPRA  CONSULTATION GRANTS ARE AWARDED COMPETITITVELY TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO MUSEUMS TO ASSIST IN THE CONSULTATION ON AND DOCUMENTATION OF NATIVE AMERICAN HUMAN REMAINS AND CULTURAL ITEMS AND TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO INDIAN TRIBES AND NATIVE HAWAIIAN ORGANIZATIONS TO ASSIST IN IDENTIFYING HUMAN REMAINS AND CULTURAL ITEMS  THE NAGPRA GRANTS ARE ADMINISTERED BY THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE  THE FEDERATED INDIANS OF GRAFTON RANCHERIA WILL CONSULT WITH THE FIELD MUSEUM IN CHICAGO, IL, REGARDING THEIR HUMAN REMAINS AND ANTHROPOLOGICAL COLLECTIONS, AND DOCUMENT ALL NAGPRA ELIGIBLE ITEMS WITH POSSIBLE CULTURAL AFFILIATION TO THE TRIBE S COAST MIWOK AND SOUTHERN POMO HERITAGE  THE RESEARCH TEAM WILL THEN PRESENT FINDINGS TO THE TRIBAL COUNCIL TO DETERMINE A PATH FORWARD TOWARDS REPATRIATION

FUNDING OPPORTUNITY NO  P22AS00103   FY 2022 NATIVE AMERICAN GRAVES PROTECTION AND REPATRIATION ACT  NAGPRA  CONSULTATION GRANTS ARE AWARDED COMPETITITVELY TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO MUSEUMS TO ASSIST IN THE CONSULTATION ON AND DOCUMENTATION OF NATIVE AMERICAN HUMAN REMAINS AND CULTURAL ITEMS AND TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO INDIAN TRIBES AND NATIVE HAWAIIAN ORGANIZATIONS TO ASSIST IN IDENTIFYING HUMAN REMAINS AND CULTURAL ITEMS  THE NAGPRA GRANTS ARE ADMINISTERED BY THE NATIONAL PARK SERVICE  THE CONFEDERATED TRIBES OF THE UMATILLA INDIAN RESERVATION  CTUIR  CULTURAL RESOURCES PROTECTION PROGRAM WILL ORGANIZE, PRIORITIZE, DIGITALLY TRANSFORM, AND CREATE A UNIQUE LIVING DATABASE OF ALL NAGPRA FILES FROM 1990 TO THE PRESENT  CURRENTLY, THE CTUIR NAGPRA FILES CONTAIN DOCUMENTS FROM MULTIPLE COMPLETED NAGPRA CLAIMS, BUT MANY CONTAIN NOTICES AND INVENTORIES THAT HAVE REMAINED UNADDRESSED DUE TO LACK OF INFORMATION ON PROVENIENCE AND CULTURAL AFFILIATION  REFLECTED IN OUR PROGRAM S MISSION STATEMENT AS IT PERTAINS TO NAGPRA, THE IMMEDIATE PRIORITY OF THE CTUIR HAS BEEN TO CONSULT, CLAIM, REPATRIATE AND REBURY ALL OUR ANCESTRAL HUMAN REMAINS AND FUNERARY OBJECTS ORIGINATING FROM THE CTUIR S CEDED AND TRADITIONAL USE LANDS RESIDING IN MUSEUM COLLECTIONS OR DISCOVERED INADVERTENTLY
